<TEXT>
a coast guard jet collided with a small plane 4000 
feet above the bahamas on saturday knocking the twinengine 
cessnas baggage compartment into the surf but causing no 
injuries authorities said 
the falcon jet was flying at about 4000 feet on a routine law 
enforcement patrol over bimini island on saturday morning when its 
tail struck the cessnas baggage compartment said lt jeff 
karonis a coast guard spokesman in miami 
the cessna carried a pilot and five san francisco science 
teachers 
considering the impact and everything everybody involved was 
very lucky said aircraft mechanic bill peck who examined the 
cessna after it safely landed in miami 
if there had been about five or 10 inches difference in the 
way the jet had hit the bottom of the plane the people on the 
plane definitely would have been killed 
the belly of the cessna was scraped where its baggage 
compartment was ripped off and about six inches of the jets upper 
tail section broke off officials said 
the federal aviation administration was investigating the 
incident karonis said 
</TEXT>
