<TEXT>
defense secretary dick cheney warned 
sunday that the clock is ticking quickly toward war with iraq 
cheney also appeared to indirectly confirm that us forces 
known to have nuclear weapons aboard naval vessels also have some 
chemical weapons capacity in the persian gulf region 
the secretary is wrapping up a fiveday visit to saudi arabia 
that included classified strategy sessions with commanders and two 
days of prechristmas troop visits 
as he had all week cheney ducked questions about whether the 
united states has decided on a timetable to attack iraq if iraqi 
president saddam hussein ignores a united nationsimposed jan 15 
deadline to withdraw from kuwait iraq overran the neighboring 
emirate on aug 2 and later annexed it 
the clock is ticking as each day goes by and he saddam does 
not withdraw his forces from kuwait cheney said 
he told reporters that the american troop deployment in the 
region was nearing the 300000 mark 
cheney refused to answer when asked directly if the united 
states has chemical weapons in the region but he referred a 
reporter back to his answer to an earlier question when he said 
president bush had available a full spectrum of weapons should 
he decide to order an attack 
on another matter cheney said he did not believe it was 
necessary for american dependents to leave the saudi arabian 
province bordering kuwait 
britain has recommended that its citizens leave saudi arabias 
eastern province by the un deadline 
but cheney said i dont believe its unsafe for people who 
are here in the eastern province of saudi arabia 
