<TEXT>
religious leaders urged prayers for 
nancy cruzan and her family saturday and called on antieuthanasia 
groups to stop trying to force the state to resume feeding the 
woman who is in a vegetative state 
her father joe cruzan said saturday that those protesting on 
his daughters behalf dont understand that if she could express 
herself she would say she does not want to live 
mark roebuck a spokesman for the missouri department of health 
said late saturday that ms cruzans condition continues to 
deteriorate and will soon be downgraded to critical she has been 
in a persistent vegetative state since she was injured in a car 
accident almost eight years ago 
doctors predicted ms cruzan 33 would die within two weeks 
after her feeding tube was removed dec 14 
her father told the joplin globe that terminal cancer patients 
in the missouri rehabilitation center where ms cruzan is a 
patient have rejected food and not been forcefed 
we believe that nancy would reject this treatment if she were 
able to make a decision he said she cant so therefore we 
have to make it for her 
antieuthanasia activists were stymied last week in asking 
various courts to force the state to resume feeding ms cruzan 
those legal setbacks snow and bitterly cold weather have 
lowered morale among some 15 demonstrators camped outside the 
missouri rehabilitation center where ms cruzan is cared for but 
spokesman andrew burnett said theyre planning on keeping the 
vigil up to the end of this ordeal 
spokesman andrew burnett director of the antiabortion and 
antieuthanasia group advocates for life said the protesters were 
planning on keeping the vigil up to the end of this ordeal 
in the meantime the rev patrick j mahoney a protestant 
minister who runs the center for christian activism in boca raton 
fla an advocacy group appealed saturday to the 8th us circuit 
court of appeals in st louis to get ms cruzans tube reconnected 
in his appeal mahoney asked the court to order the feeding tube 
reconnected until it can determine whether ms cruzans civil 
rights were violated in essence ms cruzan has been given a 
death sentence without process of the law the appeal document 
said 
the evangelical lutheran church in america the united methodist 
church the presbyterian church usa and the unitarian 
universalist association of congregations joined in issuing a 
statement supporting joe and joyce cruzan and their other two 
daughters donna and christy the cruzans are methodists 
we urge that those who are attempting to disrupt the ruling of 
the court and the wishes of nancy cruzan and her family end their 
activities and join us in respecting the judgments of the courts 
which have thoroughly examined the questions involved in the cruzan 
case and have concurred in the cruzan familys decision the 
statement said 
the statement also asked americans to lend their prayerful 
support to the family of nancy beth cruzan as they face the most 
difficult days of their life 
demonstrations at the rehabilitation center and the 19 arrests 
there tuesday only further burdened the cruzans said kay dowhower 
director of the evangelical lutheran church offices in washington 
we would hope our statement would be a sign of support and 
appreciation for how lonely death and the death process can be 
mrs dowhower said god and nature should take its own course 
what we have done in this case is prolong the suffering by 
sustaining life 
the roman catholic church also expressed support for the 
cruzans in a letter to be published sunday in the newsleader in 
springfield bishop john j leibrecht of the springfieldcape 
girardeau diocese said removing ms cruzans feeding tube was 
morally permissible 
fourteen demonstrators remained jailed saturday still invoking 
the name nancy cruzan and refusing to eat until she is fed or dies 
on friday joe cruzan presented demonstrators huddled outside 
the hospital in 15degree weather with a new coffee maker filters 
cups and an extension cord 
we are doing what we feel god has directed us to do and that 
is to carry out what we believe he told them we believe we 
are in the best position to know what would be nancys wishes 
cruzan said he appreciated their prayers and hoped the ordeal 
would be over soon 
lets all pray for a miracle that god will put an end to this 
and raise her up out of that bed and we can all go home and have a 
merry christmas he said 
