the death toll in the sinking of a charter 
ferry carrying american sailors was raised to 21 sunday and 
included one man whose body had not been recovered a us navy 
official said 
the body of the 20th victim was recovered by israeli divers 
earlier sunday haifa police said neither of the latest two 
victims was identified 
the ferry capsized saturday shortly after midnight as it was 
carrying 102 american seamen to the aircraft carrier uss saratoga 
from a christmas shore leave 
capt joseph s mobley the saratogas skipper told reporters 
sunday about the higher death toll after a tearful memorial service 
aboard the carrier 
it is 21 lives lost we still have the man whom we have not 
recovered we have the utmost confidence that he did perish 
mobley said 
about 1200 crewmen of the saratoga including the 81 survivors 
of the accident attended the memorial service in a hangar aboard 
the carrier 
two sailors dropped a wreathe into the metallic gray water from 
a hangar bay door in front of the mourners a detachment of marines 
fired three rifle salvos into the cloudy darkening sky 
some of the survivors wiped tears from their eyes as a choir 
sang america and the navy hymn eternal father 
the saratoga and its three escort ships were in the red sea as 
part of the naval buildup in the persian gulf region following 
iraqs invasion of kuwait on aug 2 
the accident was the deadliest involving us servicemen in 
operation desert shield and it raised the number of americans who 
have died to at least 74 
