<TEXT>
a railway tanker car loaded with liquid natural 
gas exploded near two passenger trains in central russia killing 
seven people and injuring 48 others tass reported sunday 
the force of the explosion blew the locomotive from one 
passenger train into the path of a second oncoming passenger train 
the official soviet news agency said carriages on both trains 
caught fire and 16 were destroyed tass said 
tass said the tanker car was sitting on a railway siding when it 
exploded at yelnikovo station near belgorod in southcentral 
russia 
a powerful blast wave struck a passenger train sitting on an 
adjacent track and threw its locomotive onto a third track into 
the path of the oncoming train it said 
all those killed were passengers on the stationery train which 
had been en route from the black sea port of kislovodsk to 
leningrad tass said the oncoming passenger train was traveling 
southeast from moscow to kharkov in the ukraine 
</TEXT>
