woman in kwamakuta near the port city of durban another man who 
died of gunshot wounds was found at dongonya about 18 miles south 
of durban 
the daily police unrest report which covers incidents from the 
previous 24 hours gave no additional details on the incidents 
more than 3000 south african blacks have died in unrest during 
1990 the worst year on record most of the deaths have occurred in 
faction fighting between rival black political groups but more 
than 200 blacks have been killed in clashes with the security 
forces 
