<TEXT>
gershom gustav schocken editor of the 
respected israeli daily haaretz for more than 50 years and one of 
the countrys most acclaimed journalists has died he was 78 
schocken died saturday at shiba hospital in tel aviv of what 
haaretz described as a malignant disease that had been 
diagnosed a year ago an editor at the hebrew daily declined to 
give further details 
schocken was born in september 1912 in zwickau germany and was 
the eldest son of shlomo salman schocken a businessman and art 
collector who established the schocken publishing houses 
he studied economics at heidelberg university from 19321933 
and with the rise of the nazis in 1933 moved to palestine where 
he worked for the anglopalestine bank 
schockens father purchased haaretz in 1937 and he became a 
business manager at the newspaper schocken was appointed editor in 
1939 and held the post till his death 
in 1955 schocken was elected to israels knesset or 
parliament as a member of the progressive party 
schocken was one of the founders of itim israels national news 
agency and he was named international editor of the year by the 
new yorkbased world press review in 1983 
there never was another journalist like schocken in israel 
a longtime haaretz reporter joel marcus wrote in sundays edition 
of the newspaper a part of schocken remains within many of us 
for him freedom of the press meant first of all the 
journalists duty to be precise to expose the establishments 
failures and not to be servile in front of it to write truly about 
a true thing and adhere to it marcus wrote 
schocken is survived by his wife a daughter and two sons his 
funeral was held sunday in tel aviv 
