income in some villages prompting calls for harsher penalties for 
smugglers and better equipment for coast guards the newspaper said 
some people also recommended improving the quality of chinese 
cigarettes to reduce demand for foreign tobacco products 
a beijing tobacco industry official told the paper that 
smuggling has caused a significant cut in state revenue from 
tobacco sales which are tightly controlled by the government 
the report said officials estimated that smugglers brought 45 
million cartons of cigarettes into china last year 
